                <head>224. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On June 14, Greek personnel attached to <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>
                    Headquarters at Izmir, Turkey, were evacuated by airlift. On June 15, the Greek
                    Government announced that as a result of anti-Greek violence on Cyprus, it was
                    severing all its military links with Turkey within <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss>’s Southeast Europe Command. Greek military units stationed
                    along the Turkish frontier were placed in a state of readiness.</p>
            </div>
